snippet.textDisplay:
im at 975 and while that particular dodge isnt a problem for me because i farm those 3 knights regularly this does point out the major issue of ds3's terrible movement consistency
some enemies slow your movements down by doing their attack animation even if they dont hit you in addition to your character somehow existing in a world where every humanoid can slide thrust 60ft at a moments notice except you 
its just frustrating at this point and would in a heartbeat give up dodge roll for the enemies movement engine and poise/posture mechanics
if it werent for the modding community's level of activity i would have uninstalled this shitshow years ago

fromsoft even went so far as to prove they can make a soulslike with a movement engine that matches the worlds with sekiro and bloodborne only to regress right back into what made ds3 frustrating and unfun in elden ring 
no fromsoft. moving like its DS2 but with a jump button while every enemy has giant super fast slidey moves that close a 60ft gap in a second while defying all logic to track you perfectly mid air is not fun nor is it a proper challenge 
its i am bread difficulty. it is octodad difficulty. you know, games that leaned on a janky movement and interaction system to generate comical mishaps for youtubers to play off of as a selling point...
